<font color="#FF0000">AIRCRAFT CARRIERS IN VIETNAM</font><br>
<tt>Tue Sep 30 23:22:10 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I don't know about books, but I served on board the USS Midway CVA41 for 9 months in 72 until the war &quot;ended&quot; in '73.  During that time (according to my DD-214) the ship and its planes were involved in 18 combat missions.  <br><br>
I do remember losing some pilots, planes and shipmates during this time.  It was odd being so far out to sea.  A routine day was four hot meals and color TV.  Of course, there was the occasionnal call to general quarters.  It was during these times that you realized all that separated you from the vast depths of ocean was a thin curtain of metal and a pilot's skill at landing a wounded bird. <br><br>
There were some very talented people in those planes.  And some very brave people on the flight deck.<br><br>
